headline: White House In No Rush To Repeal Health Law
abstract: The Department of Justice told the Supreme Court that the case did not represent an “emergency” that would require a speedy ruling.
lead_paragraph: The Trump administration came into office with its top legislative priority clear: Repeal the Affordable Care Act. It failed. Then, when a group of Republican states tried to throw out Obamacare through a lawsuit, the administration agreed that a key part of the law was unconstitutional.
keywords: Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act (2010)
